result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant Cody Tyler Johnston was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Fail/Attach Ear Tag to Deer Carcass [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 29.347(2).
  • Fail to Make Effort/Retrieve Downed Game [Modifiers: Party to a Crime]. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt:
9:05 a.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Dan Kaminsky.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Court has received numerous support letters from Atty Kaminsky's office via fax.  Statement by DA Christenson - office has been provided with them, but has not seen them, and reviews the court copies.  Atty Kaminsky has received a copy of the amended information and waives reading and enters a plea of NOT GUILTY.  Atty Kaminsky recites plea agreement, defendant will plea to count 1 with a deferred judgment and will plea to counts 4 & 6 with a fine and court costs, and requests expungement.  All other counts are to be dismissed and read-in.  State concurs and requests restitution of $200.00.  Defendant concurs.  

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty and as PTAC.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  (If felony) Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.

Defendant enters a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on count 1 of the amended information.  Court finds the defendant guilty to counts 4 and count 6.  Court orders all other counts be dismissed and read-in.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  DA confirms compliance with victim witness rights.  Statement by defendant's mother - Mary Johnston.  Sentencing statement by DA.  Sentencing statement by Atty Kaminsky.  Statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:

Count 1 -  Court orders judgment be withheld and adjourns matter pending compliance with the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.  

Count 4 - $1,000.00 fine plus court costs and includes the $750.00 DNR Surcharge.  Restitution of $200.00.  Revocation of the Chapter 29 hunting privileges for 3 years.  100 hours of community service.

Count 6 - Court costs.

Court grants the defendant 3 years to pay or payment plan and complete the community service.

Court orders Expungment upon successful completion of the Deferred Prosecution Agreement.

Court orders all other cases be dismissed.

Court adjourned at 9:35 a.m.

2:50 p.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Dan Kaminsky.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Kaminsky - an agreement has been reached, the felony count will be a plea diversion agreement and upon compliance - expungement.  Court will set for Plea & Sentencing on June 1, 2015 at 9:00 a.m.

Court adjourned at 2:52 p.m.

2:11 p.m.  No appearance by the defendant.  Attorney Dan Kaminsky present via telephone.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Kaminsky - still waiting for some Discovery from the District Attorney.  Statement by DA Christenson.  Court will set for Status Hearing on May 5, 2015 at 2:30 p.m.

Court adjourned at 2:12 p.m.

2:55 p.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Dan Kaminsky.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Kaminsky - has received some discovery and believes a resolution should be reached and requests another hearing.  Court will set for plea & sentencing on April 13, 2015 at 2:00 p.m.

Court adjourned at 2:56 p.m.
Status hearing on March 9, 2015 at 02:30 pm.

3:03 p.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Dan Kaminsky.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.

Attorney Kaminsky and defendant acknowledge receipt of the information and waives any reading.  Atty Kaminsky enters a plea of Not Guilty on behalf of the defendant.

Atty Kaminsky to schedule status hearing with the JA.

Court adjourned at 3:04 p.m.

3:17 p.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Daniel Kaminsky.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Statement by Atty Kaminsky, defendant will waive the preliminary hearing.  Defendant concurs.

Court instructs the defendant regarding his right to a preliminary examination.  Defendant waives his right to a preliminary examination.  Court accepts the waiver of the prelim and binds the defendant over for trial.

State will file the information with the court within 30 days.  Court sets for Arraignment on February 10, 2015 at 3:00 p.m.

Court adjourned at 3:20 p.m.
Status hearing on January 6, 2015 at 02:30 pm.
Status hearing on December 15, 2014 at 01:00 pm.

Atty Riepenhoff confirms receipt of the criminal complaint and waives reading.  Court instructs the defendant of the maximum penalty on each count.  Court finds probable cause.  DA makes bond recommendation.  Court sets bond at $500.00 signature bond and conditions of:  No Contact with Grant B. & Steven S.  Forms of no contact include: in person, in writing, by telephone, by e-mail, or by any other forms of electronic communication, or through a third party intending to circumvent the no contact provision. Defendant does not qualify for PD representation,  Court will set for Status Hearing in approx 2 weeks.
